🚀 Topic: How Your Monitoring System Works (Core Idea)
🧠 Simple Understanding

Think of your system like a watchman 👮‍♂️:

Servers → Watchman (your Go code) → Reports status

If everything is fine → “All good ✅”

If something fails → “Alert 🚨”

⚙️ Core Flow (Very Important)
Scheduler → Checker → Result → Database → Alert → API → Dashboard
Step-by-step:

1️⃣ Scheduler

Runs every few seconds

Triggers checks

2️⃣ Checker (Your code)

Ping / HTTP / TCP / DNS

Example:

CheckHTTP("google.com")

3️⃣ Result

Status: Online
Response: 45ms

4️⃣ Database

Stores results for history

5️⃣ Alert

Sends message if server is down

6️⃣ API

Sends data to frontend

🔥 Core Concept: Concurrency (VERY IMPORTANT)
Why Go is used?

Because of goroutines

Example:
go CheckHTTP("google.com")
go CheckPing("github.com")

👉 Both run at the same time

Real-life analogy

Instead of:

Check 1 → Wait → Check 2 → Wait → Check 3

Go does:

Check 1
Check 2
Check 3   (ALL at once 🚀)
