🎯 Placement Insight

Interview question:

👉 Why Go for monitoring systems?

Answer:

Go is used because it supports lightweight concurrency using goroutines,
which allows monitoring thousands of servers simultaneously with low memory usage.
🧩 Mini Practice (Very Important)

Try this simple program:

package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"net/http"
)

func main() {
	resp, err := http.Get("https://google.com")

	if err != nil {
		fmt.Println("Server Down ❌")
		return
	}

	defer resp.Body.Close()

	fmt.Println("Server Status:", resp.Status)
}
